FBIS4-7536 "dreeu063_h_94002" FBIS-EEU-94-063 Daily Report 1 Apr 1994 HUNGARY Jeszenszky Submits EU Membership Application Jeszenszky Submits EU Membership Application LD0104103794 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 1000 GMT 1 Apr 94 LD0104103794 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network Hungarian BFN [Report by Tivadar Keller from Athens] [Excerpt] Foreign Minister Geza Jeszenszky has officially submitted Hungary's application for European Union [EU] membership. The bid for full membership was signed by Prime Minister Peter Boross. The foreign minister handed over the document to Theodoros Pangalos, current president of the EU Council of Ministers and Greek minister in charge of European affairs. Pangalos confirmed that Greece will continue to help Hungary in the process of gaining full membership. [passage omitted]
